JSON usage rule (Erlang/OTP only)
---------------------------------

- Use Erlang/OTP built-in `json` for all JSON encoding/decoding.
- Do not add or use third-party JSON libraries (e.g., `jiffy`, `jsx`, `jsone`).
- Prefer maps as decoded representation and binaries for serialized payloads.
- Centralize JSON encode/decode helpers to ensure consistent options.

Rationale:
- Reduces dependencies and aligns with standard OTP functionality.
- Ensures consistent behavior and compatibility across environments.

Sources:
- Erlang/OTP json docs: `https://www.erlang.org/doc/apps/stdlib/json.html`

